attacks.name: Hyper Fang

attacks.text: You may discard any amount of Water Energy from your Pokémon. This attack does 60 damage for each card you discarded in this way.

attacks.text: This attack does 20 more damage for each Benched Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's).

deck.name: Radiant Greninja
rules: Radiant Pokémon Rule: You can't have more than 1 Radiant Pokémon in your deck.

abilities.name: Concealed Cards
abilities.text: You must discard an Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

attacks.name: Moonlight Shuriken
attacks.text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 90 damage to 2 of your opponent's Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

deck.flavorText: It appears and vanishes with a ninja's grace. It toys with its enemies using swift movements, while slicing them with throwing stars of sharpest water.

deck.name: Battle VIP Pass
rules: You can use this card only during your first turn.

You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Boss's Orders (Ghetsis)
rules: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Cross Switcher
rules: You must play 2 Cross Switcher cards at once. (This effect works one time for 2 cards.)
Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. If you do, switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Energy Switch
rules: Move a Basic Energy from 1 of your Pokémon to another of your Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Escape Rope
rules: Each player switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon. Your opponent switches first. (If a player does not have a Benched Pokémon, they don't switch Pokémon.)
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Hisuian Heavy Ball
rules: Look at your face-down Prize cards. You may reveal a Basic Pokémon you find there, put it into your hand, and put this Hisuian Heavy Ball in its place as a face-down Prize card. (If you don't reveal a Basic Pokémon, put this card in the discard pile.) Then, shuffle your face-down Prize cards.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Irida
rules: Search your deck for a Water Pokémon and an Item card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Melony
rules: Attach a Water Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokémon V. If you do, draw 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Nest Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Rare Candy
rules: Choose 1 of your Basic Pokémon in play. If you have a Stage 2 card in your hand that evolves from that Pokémon, put that card onto the Basic Pokémon to evolve it, skipping the Stage 1. You can't use this card during your first turn or on a Basic Pokémon that was put into play this turn.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Switch
rules: Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Ultra Ball
rules: You can use this card only if you discard 2 other cards from your hand.
Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

deck.flavorText: Close examination of its large eyes reveals that each eye is composed of a myriad of tiny eyes.

abilities.name: Flower Selecting
abilities.text: Once during your turn, if this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, you may look at the top 2 cards of your deck and put 1 of them into your hand. Put the other card in the Lost Zone.

deck.flavorText: Comfey picks flowers with its vine and decorates itself with them. For some reason, flowers won't wither once they're attached to a Comfey.

deck.flavorText: It's so strong that it can knock out some opponents in a single hit, but it also may forget what it's battling midfight.

You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Nest Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Saguaro
rules: Choose up to 2 of your Pokémon and heal 50 damage from each of them.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Sweet Honey
rules: Choose 1 of your Pokémon, and then flip a coin until you get tails. For each heads, heal 40 damage from that Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Switch
rules: Switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Switch Cart
rules: Switch your Active Basic Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon. If you do, heal 30 damage from the Pokémon you moved to your Bench.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Tool Box
rules: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. You may reveal any number of Pokémon Tool cards you find there and put them into your hand. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Town Store
rules: Once during each player's turn, that player may search their deck for a Pokémon Tool card, reveal it, and put it into their hand. Then, that player shuffles their deck.
You may play only 1 Stadium card during your turn. Put it next to the Active Spot, and discard it if another Stadium comes into play. A Stadium with the same name can't be played.

deck.name: Ultra Ball
rules: Discard 2 cards from your hand. If you do, search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Caterpie

attacks.name: Nap
attacks.text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokémon.

deck.flavorText: When attacked by bird Pokémon, it resists by releasing a terrifically strong odor from its antennae, but it often becomes their prey.

deck.name: Bunnelby

ancientTrait.name: Ω Barrage
ancientTrait.text: This Pokémon may attack twice a turn. (If the first attack Knocks Out your opponent's Active Pokémon, you may attack again after your opponent chooses a new Active Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Burrow
attacks.text: Discard the top card of your opponent's deck.

attacks.name: Rototiller
attacks.text: Shuffle a card from your discard pile into your deck.

deck.flavorText: It has ears like shovels. Digging holes strengthens its ears so much that they can sever thick roots effortlessly.

deck.name: Carnivine

attacks.name: Flick Poison
attacks.text: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. The new Active Pokémon is now Poisoned.

attacks.name: Crunch
attacks.text: Discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

deck.flavorText: It attracts prey with its sweet-smelling saliva, then chomps down. It takes a whole day to eat prey.

deck.name: Chimecho

attacks.name: Sleep Inducer
attacks.text: Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot. The new Active Pokémon is now Asleep.

deck.flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.

deck.name: Cleffa

attacks.name: Grasping Draw
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

deck.flavorText: Because of its unusual, starlike silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

deck.name: Ditto

abilities.name: Sudden Transformation
abilities.text: This Pokémon can use the attacks of any Basic Pokémon in your discard pile, except for Pokémon with a Rule Box (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes). (You still need the necessary Energy to use each attack.)

deck.flavorText: It can reconstitute its entire cellular structure to change into what it sees, but it returns to normal when it relaxes.

deck.name: Durant

attacks.name: Knock Over
attacks.text: You may discard any Stadium card in play.

attacks.name: Mountain Munch
attacks.text: Discard the top 2 cards of your opponent's deck.

deck.flavorText: They attack in groups, covering themselves in steel armor to protect themselves from Heatmor.

deck.name: Durant

attacks.name: Chip Off
attacks.text: Discard cards from your opponent's hand at random until he or she has 4 cards in his or her hand.

attacks.name: X-Scissor
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

deck.flavorText: Individuals each play different roles in driving Heatmor, their natural predator, away from their colony.

deck.name: Galarian Stunfisk

attacks.name: Field Trap
attacks.text: If your opponent has a Stadium in play, discard it. If you discarded a Stadium in this way, discard 2 Energy from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

deck.flavorText: Living in mud with a high iron content has given it a strong steel body.

deck.name: Girafarig

attacks.name: Get Lost
attacks.text: Put 2 cards from your opponent's discard pile in the Lost Zone.

attacks.name: Mind Shock
attacks.text: This attack's damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

deck.flavorText: Its tail has a small brain of its own. Beware! If you get close, it may react to your scent by biting.

deck.name: Klefki

abilities.name: Mischievous Lock
abilities.text: As long as this Pokémon is in the Active Spot, Basic Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities, except for Mischievous Lock.

attacks.name: Joust
attacks.text: Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tools from your opponent's Active Pokémon.

deck.flavorText: In the past, noble families entrusted their vault keys to a Klefki. They passed the Klefki down through the generations, taking good care of it.

deck.name: Mawile

attacks.name: Tempting Trap
attacks.text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokémon can't retreat. During your next turn, the Defending Pokémon takes 90 more damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

deck.flavorText: It uses its docile-looking face to lull foes into complacency, then bites with its huge, relentless jaws.

deck.name: Mimikyu

abilities.name: Safeguard
abilities.text: Prevent all damage done to this Pokémon by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon ex and Pokémon V.

attacks.name: Ghost Eye
attacks.text: Put 7 damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon.

deck.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in dark places untouched by sunlight. When it appears before humans, it hides itself under a cloth that resembles a Pikachu.

deck.name: Mimikyu

attacks.name: Impersonation
attacks.text: Discard a Supporter card from your hand. If you do, use the effect of that card as the effect of this attack.

attacks.name: Mischievous Hands
attacks.text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Pokémon and put 2 damage counters on each of them.

deck.flavorText: Although it's a quiet, lonely Pokémon, if you try to look at what's under its rag, it will become agitated and resist violently.

deck.name: Regieleki

attacks.name: Electromagnetic Sonar
attacks.text: Put a Trainer card from your discard pile into your hand.

attacks.name: Targeted Bolt
attacks.text: Discard 2 Lightning Energy from this Pokémon. This attack does 120 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

deck.flavorText: This Pokémon is a cluster of electrical energy. It's said that removing the rings on Regieleki's body will unleash the Pokémon's latent power.

deck.name: Sableye

attacks.name: Limitation
attacks.text: Your opponent can't play any Supporter cards from their hand during their next turn.

deck.flavorText: It's a fiend for gemstones, so it stalks Carbink. Unfortunately, Gabite almost always grabs them first.

deck.name: Shedinja

abilities.name: Shell Survival
abilities.text: Put this Pokémon into play only with the effect of Ninjask's Cast-Off Shell Ability. (When you are setting up to play, you cannot put it face down as your Active Pokémon or on your Bench.)

attacks.name: Life Squeeze
attacks.text: Put damage counters on your opponent's Active Pokémon until its remaining HP is 10.

deck.flavorText: A most peculiar Pokémon that somehow appears in a Poké Ball when a Nincada evolves.

deck.name: Tatsugiri

attacks.name: Survival Strategy
attacks.text: Search your deck for up to 2 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. You may switch this Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.

deck.flavorText: Tatsugiri is an extremely cunning Pokémon. It feigns weakness to lure in prey, then orders its partner to attack.

deck.name: Arven
rules: Search your deck for an Item card and a Pokémon Tool card, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.
deck.flavorText: Thanks to a behavior of theirs known as "synchronizing," an entire flock of these Pokémon can attack simultaneously in perfect harmony.

deck.name: Battle Compressor Team Flare Gear
rules: Search your deck for up to 3 cards and discard them. Shuffle your deck afterward.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Counter Catcher
rules: You can use this card only if you have more Prize cards remaining than your opponent.  Switch in 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon to the Active Spot.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Crushing Hammer
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Escape Rope
rules: Each player switches their Active Pokémon with 1 of their Benched Pokémon. Your opponent switches first. (If a player does not have a Benched Pokémon, they don't switch Pokémon.)
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Galar Mine
rules: The Retreat Cost of both Active Pokémon is ColorlessColorless more.
This Stadium stays in play when you play it. Discard it if another Stadium comes into play. If a Stadium with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.

deck.name: Guzma
rules: Switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon with their Active Pokémon. If you do, switch your Active Pokémon with 1 of your Benched Pokémon.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Hisuian Heavy Ball
rules: Look at your face-down Prize cards. You may reveal a Basic Pokémon you find there, put it into your hand, and put this Hisuian Heavy Ball in its place as a face-down Prize card. (If you don't reveal a Basic Pokémon, put this card in the discard pile.) Then, shuffle your face-down Prize cards.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Iono
rules: Each player shuffles their hand and puts it on the bottom of their deck. If either player put any cards on the bottom of their deck in this way, each player draws a card for each of their remaining Prize cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Lusamine
rules: Put 2 in any combination of Supporter and Stadium cards from your discard pile into your hand.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Luxurious Cape
rules: If the Pokémon this card is attached to doesn't have a Rule Box, it gets +100 HP, and if it is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokémon, that player takes 1 more Prize card. (Pokémon ex, Pokémon V, etc. have Rule Boxes.)
You may attach any number of Pokémon Tools to your Pokémon during your turn. You may attach only 1 Pokémon Tool to each Pokémon, and it stays attached.

deck.name: Miss Fortune Sisters
rules: Look at the top 5 cards of your opponent's deck and discard any number of Item cards you find there. Your opponent shuffles the other cards back into their deck.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Panic Mask
rules: Prevent all damage done to the Pokémon this card is attached to by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that have 40 HP or less remaining.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.
Attach a Pokémon Tool to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't already have a Pokémon Tool attached.

deck.name: Path to the Peak
rules: Pokémon with a Rule Box in play (both yours and your opponent's) have no Abilities. (Pokémon V, Pokémon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes.)
This Stadium stays in play when you play it. Discard it if another Stadium comes into play. If a Stadium with the same name is in play, you can't play this card.

deck.name: PokéStop
rules: Once during each player's turn, that player may discard 3 cards from the top of their deck. If a player discarded any Item cards in this way, they put those Item cards into their hand.

deck.name: Quick Ball
rules: You can play this card only if you discard another card from your hand.
Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Special Charge
rules: Shuffle 2 Special Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.
You may play as many Item cards as you like during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Double Turbo Energy
rules: As long as this card is attached to a Pokémon, it provides ColorlessColorless Energy. The attacks of the Pokémon this card is attached to do 20 less damage to your opponent's Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

deck.name: Prism Energy
rules: This card provides Colorless Energy.
If the Pokémon this card is attached to is a Basic Pokémon, this card provides every type of Energy but provides only 1 Energy at a time.

deck.name: Cleffa
rules: If this Baby Pokémon is your Active Pokémon and your opponent tries to attack, your opponent flips a coin (before doing anything required in order to use that attack). If tails, your opponent's turn ends without an attack.

attacks.name: Eeeeeeek
attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 7 cards.

deck.flavorText: Because of its unusual, star-like silhouette, people believe that it came here on a meteor.

deck.name: Croconaw

attacks.name: Sweep Away
attacks.text: Discard the top 3 cards from your deck.

deck.flavorText: It opens its huge jaws wide when attacking. If it loses any fangs while biting, they grow back in.

deck.name: Dark Golduck

attacks.name: Third Eye
attacks.text: Discard 1 Energy card attached to Dark Golduck in order to draw up to 3 cards.

deck.flavorText: When Psyducks evolve, their headaches disappear and they find themselves in possession of formidable mental powers.

deck.name: Feraligatr

abilities.name: Downpour
abilities.text: As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may discard a Water Energy card from your hand. This power can't be used if Feraligatr is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Riptide
attacks.text: Does 10 damage plus 10 damage times the number of Water Energy cards in your discard pile. Then, shuffle all Water Energy cards from your discard pile into your deck.

deck.flavorText: It is hard for it to support its own weight out of water, so it gets down on all fours. But it moves fast.

deck.name: Psyduck

attacks.name: Dizziness
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Water Gun
attacks.text: Does 20 damage plus 10 more damage for each Water Energy attached to Psyduck but not used to pay for this attack. You can't add more than 20 damage in this way.

deck.flavorText: It is often seen holding its head in its paws, as if it were suffering from a headache.

attacks.name: Shadow Images
attacks.text: Whenever Rocket's Scyther is attacked, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does no damage to Rocket's Scyther. (Any other effects of the attack still happen.) This effect lasts until Rocket's Scyther takes damage (or is Benched or is evolved).

deck.name: Totodile

attacks.name: Leer
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon can't attack Totodile during your opponent's next turn. (Benching or evolving either Pokémon ends this effect.)

attacks.name: Fury Swipes
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

deck.flavorText: Its well-developed jaws are powerful and capable of crushing anything. Even its trainer must be careful.

deck.name: Wooper

attacks.name: Amnesia
attacks.text: Choose 1 of the Defending Pokémon's attacks. That Pokémon can't use that attack during your opponent's next turn.

attacks.name: Slam
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 damage times the number of heads.

deck.flavorText: This Pokémon lives in cold water. It leaves the water to search for food when it gets cold outside.

deck.name: Focus Band
rules: Attach Focus Band to 1 of your Pokémon that doesn't have a Pokémon Tool attached to it.

If the Pokémon Focus Band is attached to would be Knocked Out by your opponent's attack, flip a coin. If heads, that Pokémon is not Knocked Out and its remaining HP become 10 instead. Then, discard Focus Band.

deck.name: Goop Gas Attack
rules: All Pokémon Powers stop working until the end of your opponent's next turn.

deck.name: Imposter Oak's Revenge
rules: Discard a card from your hand in order to play this card. Your opponent shuffles his or her hand into his or her deck, then draws 4 cards.

deck.name: Misty's Tears
rules: Discard 1 of the other cards in your hand in order to search your deck for up to 2 Water Energy cards. Show those cards to your opponent, then put them into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.

deck.name: Misty's Wrath
rules: Look at the top 7 cards of your deck. Choose 2 of those cards and put them into your hand. Discard the rest.

deck.name: Professor Elm
rules: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 7 cards. You can't play any more Trainer cards this turn.

deck.name: Rocket's Sneak Attack
rules: Look at your opponent's hand. If he or she has any Trainer cards, choose 1 of them. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

deck.name: Secret Mission
rules: Look at your opponent's hand. Then, you may discard as many other cards as you want from your hand and draw that many cards.

deck.name: The Rocket's Trap
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, choose up to 3 cards at random from your opponent's hand (don't look at them). Your opponent shuffles those cards into his or her deck.

deck.name: Trash Exchange
rules: Count the number of cards in your discard pile and shuffle them into your deck. Then discard that many cards from the top of your deck.

deck.name: Rainbow Energy
rules: Attach Rainbow Energy to 1 of your Pokémon. While in play, Rainbow Energy counts as every type of basic Energy but only provides 1 Energy at a time. (Doesn't count as a basic Energy card when not in play.) When you attach this card from your hand to 1 of your Pokémon, it does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance.)

deck.name: Stufful
deck.flavorText: Despite its adorable appearance, when it gets angry and flails about, its arms and legs could knock a pro wrestler sprawling.

attacks.name: Heat Tackle
attacks.text: Blaine's Arcanine does 10 damage to itself.

attacks.name: Firestorm
attacks.text: Discard 3 Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Arcanine in order to use this attack.

attacks.name: Roaring Flames
attacks.text: Discard all Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charizard. If all Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charizard provide 2 Fire Energy, discard all of them. This attack does 20 damage plus 20 more damage for each Fire Energy discarded in this way.

attacks.name: Flame Jet
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 40 damage to that Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

attacks.name: Fire Tail Slap
attacks.text: Use this attack only if there are any Fire Energy cards attached to Blaine's Charmander. Flip a coin. If tails, discard 1 of those cards.

attacks.name: Bonfire
attacks.text: Flip 3 coins. For each heads, discard 1 Fire Energy card attached to Blaine's Charmeleon. If you can't discard Energy cards, this attack does nothing. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads to each of your opponent's Pokémon. Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for this attack. (Any other effects that would happen after applying Weakness and Resistance still happen.)

attacks.name: Stoke
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Fire Energy card and attach it to Blaine's Growlithe. Shuffle your deck afterward.

attacks.name: Body Slam
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, the Defending Pokémon is now Paralyzed.

attacks.text: Shuffle your hand into your deck, then draw 7 cards.

deck.name: Cyndaquil

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

deck.flavorText: It is very meek and constantly crouches in a defensive posture. When threatened, it protects itself with the flame on its back.

deck.name: Quilava

attacks.name: Smokescreen
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon tries to attack during your opponent's next turn, your opponent flips a coin. If tails, that attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Char
attacks.text: If the Defending Pokémon doesn't have a Char counter on it, flip a coin. If heads, put a Char counter on it. A Char counter requires your opponent to flip a coin after every turn. If tails, put 2 damage counters on the Pokémon with that Char counter. (Char counters stay on the Pokémon as long as it's in play.)

deck.flavorText: Be careful if it turns its back during battle. It means that it will attack with the fire on its back.

deck.name: Typhlosion

abilities.name: Fire Recharge
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Fire Pokémon. This power can't be used if Typhlosion is Asleep, Confused, or Paralyzed.

attacks.name: Flame Burst
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 60 damage plus 20 more damage and does 20 damage to Typhlosion. If tails, this attack does 60 damage.

deck.flavorText: If its rage peaks, it becomes so hot that anything that touches it will instantly go up in flames.

deck.name: Blaine
rules: During this turn, instead of attaching your free Energy card, you may instead attach 2 Fire Energy cards to 1 of your Pokémon with Blaine in its name. (Playing additional copies of this card this turn has no effect.)

deck.name: Cinnabar City Gym
rules: This card stays in play after being played. Discard this card if another Stadium card comes into play.
Ignore Weakness when a Water Pokémon does damage to a Pokémon with Blaine in its name.

deck.name: Energy Flow
rules: For each of your Pokémon, you may return any number of Energy cards attached to it to your hand.

deck.name: Fervor
rules: Show the top 3 cards of your deck to all players. Put any Fire Energy cards there into your hand and discard the rest.

deck.name: Focus Band

rules: Choose up to 3 Basic Pokémon cards, Evolution cards, and/or basic Energy cards from your discard pile. Show them to your opponent and shuffle them into your deck.

deck.name: Pokémon Center
rules: Remove all damage counters from all of your own Pokémon with damage counters on them, then discard all Energy cards attached to those Pokémon.

deck.name: Rocket's Sneak Attack
rules: Look at your opponent's hand. If he or she has any Trainer cards, choose 1 of them. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

deck.name: The Rocket's Trap
rules: Flip a coin. If heads, choose up to 3 cards at random from your opponent's hand (don't look at them). Your opponent shuffles those cards into his or her deck.

deck.name: Warp Point
rules: If your opponent has any Benched Pokémon, he or she chooses 1 of them and switches it with his or her Active Pokémon, then, if you have any Benched Pokémon, you switch 1 of them with your Active Pokémon.

deck.name: Professor Kukui
rules: Draw 2 cards. During this turn, your Pokémon's attacks do 20 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn (before your attack).

deck.name: Audino

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

deck.flavorText: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures' feelings and physical conditions.

deck.name: Chansey

attacks.name: Egg Rolling
attacks.text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 60 damage for each heads.

deck.flavorText: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

deck.name: Electrode
deck.flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

deck.name: Farfetch'd

attacks.name: Package Deal
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

deck.flavorText: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

deck.name: Herdier
deck.flavorText: The black fur that covers this Pokémon's body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.

deck.name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

deck.flavorText: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

deck.name: Kilowattrel

attacks.name: Jet Wing
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

deck.flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

deck.name: Lillipup
deck.flavorText: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won't forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.

deck.name: Miraidon

attacks.name: Lightning Laser
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

deck.flavorText: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

deck.name: Pikachu ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dynamic Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

deck.name: Tynamo
deck.flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

deck.name: Voltorb
deck.flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

deck.name: Wattrel

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

deck.flavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

deck.name: Zangoose
deck.flavorText: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

rules: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Youngster
rules: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 5 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Paras
deck.flavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

deck.flavorText: It walks carefully to prevent its egg from breaking. However, it is extremely fast at running away.

deck.name: Electrode
deck.flavorText: The more energy it charges up, the faster it gets. But this also makes it more likely to explode.

deck.name: Farfetch'd

attacks.name: Package Deal
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

deck.flavorText: They use a plant stalk as a weapon, but not all of them use it in the same way. Several distinct styles of stalk fighting have been observed.

deck.name: Herdier
deck.flavorText: The black fur that covers this Pokémon's body is dense and springy. Even sharp fangs bounce right off.

deck.name: Kangaskhan

attacks.name: Spike Draw
attacks.text: Draw 2 cards.

deck.flavorText: There are records of a lost human child being raised by a childless Kangaskhan.

deck.name: Kilowattrel

attacks.name: Jet Wing
attacks.text: During your next turn, this Pokémon can't attack.

deck.flavorText: Kilowattrel inflates its throat sac to amplify its electricity. By riding the wind, this Pokémon can fly over 430 miles in a day.

deck.name: Lillipup
deck.flavorText: This Pokémon is far brighter than the average child, and Lillipup won't forget the love it receives or any abuse it suffers.

deck.name: Miraidon

attacks.name: Lightning Laser
attacks.text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

deck.flavorText: Much remains unknown about this creature. It resembles Cyclizar, but it is far more ruthless and powerful.

deck.name: Pikachu ex
rules: Pokémon ex rule: When your Pokémon ex is Knocked Out, your opponent takes 2 Prize cards.

attacks.name: Dynamic Bolt
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, discard all Energy from this Pokémon.

deck.name: Tynamo
deck.flavorText: While one alone doesn't have much power, a chain of many Tynamo can be as powerful as lightning.

deck.name: Voltorb
deck.flavorText: It rolls to move. If the ground is uneven, a sudden jolt from hitting a bump can cause it to explode.

deck.name: Wattrel

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

deck.flavorText: When its wings catch the wind, the bones within produce electricity. This Pokémon dives into the ocean, catching prey by electrocuting them.

deck.name: Zangoose
deck.flavorText: The eggs it lays are filled with happiness. Eating even one bite will bring a smile to anyone.

deck.name: Electric Generator
rules: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck and attach up to 2 Basic Lightning Energy cards you find there to your Benched Lightning Pokémon in any way you like. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Energy Retrieval
rules: Put up to 2 Basic Energy cards from your discard pile into your hand.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Energy Search
rules: Search your deck for a Basic Energy card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Nemona
rules: Draw 3 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Nest Ball
rules: Search your deck for a Basic Pokémon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Potion
rules: Heal 30 damage from 1 of your Pokémon.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Professor's Research (Professor Turo)
rules: Discard your hand and draw 7 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Ultra Ball
rules: You can use this card only if you discard 2 other cards from your hand. Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
You may play any number of Item cards during your turn.

deck.name: Youngster
rules: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 5 cards.
You may play only 1 Supporter card during your turn.

deck.name: Paras
deck.flavorText: No matter how much it eats, the mushrooms growing on its back steal away most of the nutrients it consumes.

deck.name: Audino

attacks.name: Find a Friend
attacks.text: Search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

deck.flavorText: This Pokémon has a kind heart. By touching with its feelers, Audino can gauge other creatures' feelings and physical conditions.
